.TH IFSX 1 "2026" "ifsx @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ifsx \- IFS Extract/Repack Tool for QNX images
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ifsx
.I command
[\fB\-h\fR] [\fIarguments\fR]
.PP
.B ifsx extract
[\fB\-\-pre\-extract\fR \fIhook\fR].\|.\|.
[\fB\-\-post\-extract\fR \fIhook\fR].\|.\|.
.I image.ifs output\-dir
.PP
.B ifsx pack
[\fB\-\-pre\-pack\fR \fIhook\fR].\|.\|.
[\fB\-\-post\-pack\fR \fIhook\fR].\|.\|.
.I extracted\-dir
[\fIoutput.ifs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ifsx
extracts and repacks QNX IFS (Image Filesystem) boot images. It is a
wrapper around the
.BR dumpifs (1)
and
.BR mkifs (1)
tools from the QNX Software Development Platform (SDP).
.PP
Both tools must be present in
.B PATH
before invoking
.BR ifsx .
Source the QNX SDP environment script before use, for example:
.PP
.RS
source ~/qnx800/qnxsdp-env.sh
.RE
.PP
If either tool is not found at startup,
.B ifsx
will print:
.PP
.RS
Warning: dumpifs and/or mkifs not found. Did you source the SDP?
.RE
.PP
At startup
.B ifsx
creates
.B ~/.ifsx/
and its four subdirectories
.RI ( pre-extract ,
.IR post-extract ,
.IR pre-pack ,
.IR post-pack )
if they do not already exist. Executable files placed in those directories
are available as hooks (see
.B HOOKS
below).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BR extract ", " x
Extract an IFS image to a self-contained directory. Produces the
extracted filesystem tree along with
.I _ifsx.build
(buildfile contract) and
.I _ifsx.meta
(image metadata), both required for repacking.
.TP
.BR pack ", " p
Repack an extracted directory back into an IFS image. The directory
must contain the
.I _ifsx.build
file generated by
.BR extract .
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "extract"
.TP
.I image.ifs
Path to the IFS image to extract.
.TP
.I output\-dir
Directory where the extracted files will be written.
Created if it does not exist.
.TP
\fB\-\-pre\-extract\fR \fIhook\fR
Name of an executable in
.B ~/.ifsx/pre-extract/
to run before extraction. May be repeated; hooks execute in the order
given on the command line. Each hook receives
.I image.ifs
and
.I output-dir
as positional arguments. A non-zero exit code aborts the operation.
.TP
\fB\-\-post\-extract\fR \fIhook\fR
Name of an executable in
.B ~/.ifsx/post-extract/
to run after extraction. Same semantics as
.BR \-\-pre\-extract .
.SS "pack"
.TP
.I extracted\-dir
Path to the directory previously created by
.BR "ifsx extract" .
Must contain
.IR _ifsx.build .
.TP
.I output.ifs
Path for the output IFS image.
Defaults to
.I extracted\-dir
with
.B .ifs
appended.
.TP
\fB\-\-pre\-pack\fR \fIhook\fR
Name of an executable in
.B ~/.ifsx/pre-pack/
to run before packing. May be repeated; hooks execute in the order
given on the command line. Each hook receives
.I output.ifs
and
.I extracted-dir
as positional arguments. A non-zero exit code aborts the operation.
.TP
\fB\-\-post\-pack\fR \fIhook\fR
Name of an executable in
.B ~/.ifsx/post-pack/
to run after packing. Same semantics as
.BR \-\-pre\-pack .
.SH HOOKS
.B ifsx
supports user-defined hook executables stored under
.BR ~/.ifsx/ :
.PP
.RS
.nf
~/.ifsx/
    pre-extract/    run before extraction
    post-extract/   run after extraction
    pre-pack/       run before packing
    post-pack/      run after packing
.fi
.RE
.PP
Any executable file placed in one of these directories becomes a hook.
Hooks are called with two positional arguments:
.PP
.RS
.IP 1. 3
The IFS image path (absolute)
.IP 2. 3
The directory path (absolute)
.RE
.PP
For
.B extract
hooks both arguments refer to the source image and output directory.
For
.B pack
hooks the first argument is the output IFS path and the second is the
extracted directory.
.PP
If a hook exits with a non-zero code the operation is aborted immediately
and the remaining hooks in the chain are not executed.
Both stdout and stderr of the hook are printed to the terminal.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PATH
Must include the directory containing
.B dumpifs
and
.BR mkifs .
Source the QNX SDP environment script to populate this.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Extract an IFS image:
.RS
ifsx extract image.ifs output/
.RE
.PP
Extract, running hooks before and after:
.RS
ifsx extract \-\-pre\-extract validate \-\-post\-extract sign image.ifs output/
.RE
.PP
Repack with an explicit output path:
.RS
ifsx pack output/ new_image.ifs
.RE
.PP
Repack using the default output name
.RI ( output.ifs ):
.RS
ifsx pack output/
.RE
.PP
Repack with a post-pack hook:
.RS
ifsx pack \-\-post\-pack deploy output/ new_image.ifs
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dumpifs (1),
.BR mkifs (1)
